            . On the 10th of July this handkerchief was taken from the door - it was brought to me about six o'clock in the evening; I had seen it safe at two.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-282-person2339">
                  GABRIEL 
                  BURROWS
               <interp inst="t18300916-282-person2339" type="surname" value="BURROWS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-282-person2339" type="given" value="GABRIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-282-person2339" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to a pawnbroker. The prisoner came to me with the handkerchief, and wanted 1s. 6d. or 2s. for it - I think our house is three quarters of a mile from the prosecutor's; I questioned him - he said it was his mother's, and she had bought it at Mr. Mill's, in Kingsland-road; I asked what this was at the corner - he said, "That is where my mother ties up her money;" I then saw some pin-holes, and then said,"Is this where your mother ties up her money?" - I went to the door, and he ran out; I pursued him twenty yards, gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner pleaded distress, and received a good character.</p>
               <p>
